The paper deals with the problem of Multi-agent Path Finding (MAPF), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm is designed for coordination among multiple agents, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the decentralization of the algorithm, which can be related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Finally, the algorithm can be applied to various domains, including automated warehouses and transportation systems, which can be categorized under Systems and Control (cs.SY).
